0. Additional Definitions.

As used herein, "this License" refers to version 3 of the GNU Lesser
General Public License, and the "GNU GPL" refers to version 3 of the GNU
General Public License.

"The Library" refers to a covered work governed by this License,
other than an Application or a Combined Work as defined below.

An "Application" is any work that makes use of an interface provided
by the Library, but which is not otherwise based on the Library.
Defining a subclass of a class defined by the Library is deemed a mode
of using an interface provided by the Library.

A "Combined Work" is a work produced by combining or linking an
Application with the Library. The particular version of the Library
with which the Combined Work is made is also called the "Linked
Version".

The "Minimal Corresponding Source" for a Combined Work means the
Corresponding Source for the Combined Work, minus the source code
for portions of the Combined Work, other than those portions that are
independent based on their interfaces with the Application.

The "Corresponding Application Code" for a Combined Work means the
object code and/or source code for the Application, including any data
and utility programs needed for reproducing the Combined Work from the
Application, but excluding the System Libraries of the Combined Work.

1. Exception to Section 3 of the GNU GPL.

You may convey a covered work under sections 3 and 4 of this License
without being bound by section 3 of the GNU GPL.

2. Conveying Modified Versions.

If you modify a copy of the Library, and, in your modifications, a
facility refers to a function or data to be supplied by an Application
that uses the facility (other than as an argument passed when the
facility is invoked), then you may convey a copy of the modified
version under this License, provided that you do both of the following:

a) The work must itself be a library or an application, but with C.
below.

b) You must cause the files modified to carry prominent notices
stating that you changed the files and the date of any change.

c) You must cause the whole of the work to be licensed at no
charge to all third parties under the terms of this License.

3. Combined Works.

You may convey a Combined Work under terms of your choice that,
in combination, do not restrict modification of the portions of the
Library contained in the Combined Work and reverse engineering for
debugging such modifications, if you also do each of the following:

a) Give prominent notice with each copy of the Combined Work that
the Library is used in it and that the Library and its use are
covered by this License.

b) Cause the Combined Work to carry complete source code for the
Library and the Application, on a medium customarily used for
software interchange.

c) For an Application, display, as appropriate, copyright notice(s)
for your Application. We recommend that if your application does
interactive display of copyright notice, the notice should include
entry for at least the most prominent features or user selections
within the application. That is not required to list claims or
describe all relationship of other entities.

d) Do one of the following under the terms of the GNU GPL:

1) Under version 3 of the GNU GPL, relying on the exception in
2c above.

2) Under a prior version of this License, if applicable, as
published by Free Software Foundation.

e) For a Combined Work that displays copyright notices during
execution, include the copyright notice for the Library among these
notices, as well as a reference directing the user to the copies of
this License provided by Licensor.

f) Do one of the following:

1) Convey the Minimal Corresponding Source under the terms of
this License, and under section 6 of the GNU GPL for all code in
the Combined Work that is covered by neither section 3 of the GNU
GPL nor section 2b of this License.

2) Convey under section 6 of the GNU GPL all code for the
covered works, with all linking and compilation of those works
facilitated. Special exception for Smaller works shall be provided
if such works are conveyable without option. For works that link
with libraries licensed under this License, you should provide
symbol information for the executable forms of such works.

